reviewText: My son loves Elmo's world, so I purchased this DVD set for him. It is a great set and has a lot of variety. The menu allows you to choose the episodes seperately, but overall each DVD is about an hour long. This is great for an Elmo's world fan!!
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: My 2 year old loves Elmo. This dvd helps me by not having to fast forward through Sesame Street to the Elmo's World part.
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: These are such great episodes. The dvd was perfect and my son still loves all these shows. Buy it, you don't get any better than this!
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: my 19 month old likes these three dvds but parts are too intense for him. He doesn't like Mr Banana or Prince Charming.  HE loves Mr Noodle, Mr Noodle's brother Mr Noodle and Mr Noodle's sister Miss Noodle.  He cheers for them.  So buy this one but skip the scary parts.
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: My 20-month old daughter LOVES Elmo!  She will watch any episode of Elmo's World over and over again.  This set is a great deal!  3 dvds for $20.  You can't beat the price.
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: My daughter has had it for years and is now gonna be 7 in 3days and still loves her Elmo and wont give it up.  Anything educational is a 2thumbs up with me!!!
Title: Best of Elmo's World

reviewText: Taught and helped my stubborn as a mule, two year old to use spoon, fork and eat!!  Oh my I could hug Elmo!!!

reviewText: I just dont have words to explain, the way my two years little boy has reacted ever since y got him this set of DVD'S,i think he has requested to wacht it over 10 times a week,and the reaction is the same al the time,i enjoy just to wacht him gigle and smile seing Elmo doing is best,i definetly recomend it to any Parents that would like to be able to do chores at home and the kids stay out of their way.

reviewText: Bought this for our grand-daughter's 2nd Birthday, making her very happy. She got all things Elmo and loved them all.
